<subSubSection id="B64FA5A3959440A97E4D20E0D3B09A4F" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="146749E5FA91E25F61B8BB43576672C5" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC612D18D51C6250311B01F13DC1B7F2" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">In honour of George Hans Emmo Wolfgang Hieronymus (1846-1921), German botanist, sometimes resident of Argentina.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CF6E1E775D8D0AE5D0FE37090F8DAEBE" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" type="common names">
<paragraph id="D3D25B1A33BDF3D2EB13D8CF9BA8FCC3" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Common names.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D82C2B25411CA6DC52FC90CB16A551C" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Seringuilla, sivinga (Tucuman).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3D238795E8C5565347AE61F429581E8F" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" type="taxonomy">
<paragraph id="F781055E6202DFA4F6834E8A8CB1F3E8" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Taxonomy.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C04C8BA4D812D7AF8980FA15EC544E4" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">
This species contains substantial variation in the robustness of the plants. 
<bibRefCitation id="2CC8DA1DFCC04C7A694051EEC5362B07" author="Conert, J" journalOrPublisher="Cramer, Weinheim" pageId="26" pageNumber="65" refId="B5" refString="Conert, J, 1961. Die Systematik und Anatomie der Arundineae. J. Cramer, Weinheim" title="Die Systematik und Anatomie der Arundineae. J." year="1961">Conert (1961)</bibRefCitation>
partitioned this variation into three species (
<taxonomicName id="A90D681D5AAD7E0889E16C9D605EB9BC" authority="Pilger, 1906" authorityName="Hitchc" authorityYear="1923" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lamprothyrsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lamprothyrsus peruvianus" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peruvianus">
<emphasis id="BF510C752704AE8717D79CCB0E7DBB2B" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Lamprothyrsus peruvianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="20FE13170D7B9B3E91012A426267B1EF" authority="Pilger, 1906" authorityName="Pilger" authorityYear="1906" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lamprothyrsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lamprothyrsus venturi" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="venturi">
<emphasis id="69759DE080F1D8DA98DCDC4DEE082898" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Lamprothyrsus venturi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8A787DBCA815164874C63AE137B3F4FE" authority="Pilger, 1906" authorityName="Testoni &amp; Linder" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lamprothyrsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lamprothyrsus hieronymi" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hieronymi">
<emphasis id="551CD8B1A9D54EF7EAFCD935F05A16E3" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Lamprothyrsus hieronymi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="C006C2BDC8AFF69939C5E40F6CF91756" author="Pilger, R" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Beiblatt" pageId="27" pageNumber="66" pagination="58 - 67" refId="B28" refString="Pilger, R, 1906. Lamprothyrsus, eine neue Gattung der Graeser und ihre Verwandten. Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Beiblatt 85: 58 - 67" title="Lamprothyrsus, eine neue Gattung der Graeser und ihre Verwandten." volume="85" year="1906">Pilger (1906)</bibRefCitation>
recognized varieties in his 
<taxonomicName id="B1FE7D0DF2DBF16F69B5086B8581DF7E" authority="Pilger, 1906" authorityName="Testoni &amp; Linder" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lamprothyrsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lamprothyrsus hieronymi" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hieronymi">
<emphasis id="744638145FA3499C1B9DE874EC239365" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Lamprothyrsus hieronymi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Study of the herbarium material suggests that this is most likely all one taxon (
<bibRefCitation id="E755E546198B31BDB50EECB325704BD8" author="Bernardello, LM" journalOrPublisher="Kurtziana" pageId="26" pageNumber="65" pagination="119 - 132" refId="B4" refString="Bernardello, LM, 1979. Sobre del genero Lamprothyrsus (Poaceae) en Argentina. Kurtziana 12-13: 119 - 132" title="Sobre del genero Lamprothyrsus (Poaceae) en Argentina." volume="12 - 13" year="1979">Bernardello 1979</bibRefCitation>
), but an analysis of variation within natural populations in the field would be useful to understand the range of variation possible. 
<taxonomicName id="78E8466F07E26FEEA3EF5925281F8B93" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia hieronymi" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hieronymi">
<emphasis id="DA575568AF55AD7D403DCF3F380ECEA2" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Cortaderia hieronymi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other species in 
<taxonomicName id="F01CD1CEBD09FCA776D6521506C91546" authorityName="Testoni &amp; Linder" authorityYear="2017" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0D2459BD735A3F4B97E85DFF527341B1" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Cortaderia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the very long hair-like lemma awns and setae, the glumes without veins, and the small flowers with relatively short and sparse lemma hair.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD11BEBCCED1F74287DEB0B61F1DB532" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">
Only apomictic populations are known, but a few fertile staminate specimens with long hairs on the lemmas were found (
<bibRefCitation id="A9BDF88A47B261CE628BF671834F3BBC" author="Bernardello, LM" journalOrPublisher="Kurtziana" pageId="26" pageNumber="65" pagination="119 - 132" refId="B4" refString="Bernardello, LM, 1979. Sobre del genero Lamprothyrsus (Poaceae) en Argentina. Kurtziana 12-13: 119 - 132" title="Sobre del genero Lamprothyrsus (Poaceae) en Argentina." volume="12 - 13" year="1979">Bernardello 1979</bibRefCitation>
). It is not known if they can form viable caryopses, and if the species is dioecious or gynodioecious.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3CA575935D512D35459F98A391BEDB3E" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">
In the central and northern Argentina to Ecuador 
<taxonomicName id="6C2115D0730EF9506400CB0F5425B8AB" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia hieronymi" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hieronymi">
<emphasis id="C1D6F6BD05EAB5765C439E7DCEE035C6" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Cortaderia hieronymi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sympatric with the two subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="311B8570FBE919B3E6672E918C21EAC8" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia selloana" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloana">
<emphasis id="8C804D4744E4000DF3CADEADE6A11B5B" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Cortaderia selloana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is easily separated by its smaller panicles, spikelets with glumes without veins, and 5-veined, 3-awned lemmas. In Peru and Ecuador it 
<pageBreakToken id="0255D8FA6422E5E15AA67D519D890923" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" start="start">is</pageBreakToken>
sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="5E63D0FE49A89A547853ED1F19C7B71A" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia bifida" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifida">
<emphasis id="EB240580DE64E12DCCB83415544D2DC5" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Cortaderia bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which it is often confused: in both species the old leaf sheaths are lacerated and the spikelets have long awns, but the spikelets of 
<taxonomicName id="ED53DACE8FB143BC36E3C242472E2DAB" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia hieronymi" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hieronymi">
<emphasis id="8F291141F152DB2B68215C2D920A606F" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Cortaderia hieronymi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are bigger, and the lemmas with longer and robust central awns.
</paragraph>
